16951.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16951.description: Patrick invents a new board game, and invites SpongeBob, Sandy and Squidward to play it with him. // After accidentally flushing Mr. Krabs’ safe, SpongeBob and Squidward must go into the sewers to find it.

16952.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
16952.description: Aang and the kids finally arrive in Ba Sing Se to see the Earth King, only to find mysterious forces within the city conspiring to stop them. Meanwhile, Jet tries to find proof that Zuko and Uncle are Fire Nation.

16953.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
16953.description: A series of short stories, highlighting different characters and their individual adventures in the city. Tales of Katara and Toph, Uncle, Sokka, Aang, Zuko, and Momo.

16954.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16954.description: SpongeBob adopts a stray worm, and to his surprise, the worm gives birth to some worm babies overnight! But since Gary won’t play nice, SpongeBob needs to find loving homes for his new slimey, weird-looking friends. // Plankton is sick of Karen’s criticisms, so he decides he can just replace her with some new computer inventions! But when he takes them out on a Krabby Patty formula-stealing mission, he learns that Karen truly is one of a kind.

16955.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16955.description: SpongeBob is left in charge of the Krusty Krab while Mr. Krabs steps out for 15 minutes, and he is determined to make it the best-managed 15 minutes ever! / SpongeBob's got a full day, and he's determined to do everything he's scheduled to do: help fix Mr. Krabs' telescope, go to Patrick's birthday party, and help with Sandy's science presentation.

16956.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16956.description: After an accident, Donnie finds himself slowly losing his intelligence.

16957.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16957.description: The Turtles are baited by an unknown enemy into deadly traps.

16958.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16958.description: Po saves a girl from some bandits, only to learn that she's engaged to be married to the Dragon Warrior.

16959.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16959.description: During a fight with Tong Fo, Po is struck by lightning, giving him the power to read minds.

16960.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16960.description: When Rico gets a freaky fortune from his cookie, he initially ignores it. Julien sets out to make Rico's fortune come true. // A female chimp named Lulu arrives at the zoo for a short stay, and Phil is smitten. Unfortunately, Lulu falls for Mason.

16961.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16961.description: On watch-duty, Private sees a terrifying Skorka: a sky orca whale. No one believes it exists, so Private sets out to battle the Sorka on his own. // When the penguins are interrupted mid-operation by a nosey scientist, they leave the zoo in danger.

16962.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16962.description: Mr. Krabs and Plankton have been business rivals and bitter enemies for longer than anyone can remember. But one day, Mr. Krabs reveals that they were not always this way. There was a time when the two rivals were best friends.

16963.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16963.description: Mr. Krab's old fry cook pays a special visit to the Krusty Krab. SpongeBob is in awe of his predecessor, who has since become a world renowned chef following his departure from Krabs' restaurant. // Tales of the boogeyman sends SpongeBob into panic. Every dark corner in his house could be a potential hiding place for the infamous monster.

16964.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16964.description: Determined to uncover Plankton’s next devious plot, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on him. // Watch an instructional video on boating techniques with Squidward and SpongeBob. // Mr. Krabs holds a contest for his employees: The first one to learn the names of every Krusty Krab customer wins a tropical vacation.

16965.title: Nella The Princess Knight
16965.description: Nella helps Queen Mom and Grammy on a hazardous journey to a prestigious sports tournament. // Riley invites Nella on a tour of her kingdom but is more interested in getting a winning picture than enjoying the sights with her friend.

16966.title: Nella The Princess Knight
16966.description: When Castlehaven loses its sparkle, Nella and the Knights of the Sparkly Table face their toughest quest yet to get it back. // Nella's family vacation to Lake Twinkle is interrupted by Tricksy.

16967.title: Bubble Guppies
16967.description: The Spring Chicken is about to announce the arrival of spring, but first, she needs a beautiful flower. Help the Bubble Guppies figure out how to plant and care for a flower.

16968.title: Bubble Guppies
16968.description: Glide through the aisles of the supermarket with the Bubble Guppies as they shop for fruits, vegetables and the last box of Bubble Bites for Bubble Puppy!

16969.title: Dora the Explorer
16969.description: ¡Falta algo! Something's missing! Dora and Boots meet a wizard, El Encantador, who's missing his magic wand! Dora and Boots set off to find El Encantador's wand so he can do his magic.

16970.title: Dora the Explorer
16970.description: Squeaky, squeaky! What's that sound? It's Squeaky, Boots' adorably squeezable new bath toy. But when Boots loses Squeaky, we all have to head to the Gooey Geyser to get him back.

16971.title: Rusty Rivets
16971.description: Rusty builds rocket skates instead of learning how to skate but these cut up the ice and end up stranding all his friends on ice floes. // When Ralph (Liam's toy) goes missing in the woods, Rusty and Ruby join the hunt. Alas, they all get lost, and have to find a way home without Rusty's usual tools to help them!

16972.title: Rusty Rivets
16972.description: Rusty and Ruby make Ranger Anna a robotic pet, but it goes haywire when they try to program it. // Rusty builds Liam a spaceship as a surprise, but instead of impressing him, it wreaks havoc on the town.

16973.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
16973.description: When Starla the friendly cowgirl truck loses one of her pistons, Blaze and AJ set out to get it back. But they’ll have to hurry before Crusher gets his greedy tires on it!

16974.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
16974.description: Gabby is the mechanic all the Monster Machines in town count on to fix them up. But when Crusher steals all her tools, Gabby needs Blaze's help to get them back!

16975.title: PAW Patrol
16975.description: It’s a hot day and the pups head for the water park – but the pool is empty! Paw Patrol to the rescue. Digger and Rocky step in and help Ryder get water to the pool. Pool Day is back on!/When the animals don’t show up in time for the Circus to start; Ryder and the Paw Patrol step in to help.

16976.title: PAW Patrol
16976.description: Rubble is pretending to be a super pup but get’s himself in some trouble. Ryder and the Paw Patrol have to save Rubble! // When Ryder’s Robot Pup breaks and starts going wild around Adventure Bay, it takes the whole Paw Patrol to help Ryder find it.

16977.title: PAW Patrol
16977.description: When Mandy the monkey escapes from her cage on the train, Ryder and the PAW Patrol are lead on a wild chase through Adventure Bay! // During a bad wind storm, Ryder and the PAW Patrol have to save an Owl trapped in a blown over tree and reunite her with “Little Hootie”, her baby.

16978.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16978.description: SpongeBob and Pat are fascinated by the snow they see inside the Treedome and want to play in it, but sandy is hibernating for the winter. // One day, Gary starts following Pat around and SpongeBob can't figure out why. At first, it doesn't bother him, but slowly he grows more and more jealous and becomes determined to win Gary back.

16979.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16979.description: SpongeBob attempts and fails his driving test again, but a ragged and fed up Ms. Puff wants him out of her classroom so she makes up some bogus extra credit for him so he can pass the test. // When SpongeBob and Pat go to a jellyfishing convention, SpongeBob tries to join an exclusive, elitist jellyfishing club. Secretly, the club president thinks SpongeBob is not worthy.

16980.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16980.description: When Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy go away for the weekend, they ask SpongeBob and Pat to house sit for them. Inside the house, SpongeBob and Pat discover the evil super villain, Man-Ray frozen in a tank. // SpongeBob becomes an overnight stand up comedy sensation when he starts telling derogatory jokes about squirrels. At first, Sandy is a good sport, but soon people start treating her as if she really was stupid and smelly.

16981.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16981.description: The Commissioner flips his lid, literally. His toupee blows off and sticks to Maurice, who also gets red cheeks and a skinned tail, all by accident. Julien and Mort chase him with sticks, intent on beating the “monster” stuck to Maurice’s head. The baboon ladies take Maurice in, protecting and pampering him because they mistakenly think he’s a male baboon. It’s up to the penguins to get the toupee back and restore it to its rightful scalp. // Shelly the ostrich gets stuck in drying cement and only Rico can save her. Shelly falls for him hard as a result, however, Rico’s heart forever belongs to his doll. Shelly swipes the doll and tries hard to win his heart, but Rico doesn’t budge and his doll is accidently hauled off in a recycle truck. The penguins give chase but are left hopelessly in the dust. Shelly, wanting to make amends, tosses them on her back and sprints after the truck – can she possibly catch it?

16982.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16982.description: The penguin’s worst nightmare has come true. After a sailing trip gone wrong they wind up in the Hoboken Zoo. Strangely, the animals are happy, the zoo is a paradise, and life couldn’t be better! Zookeeper Frances takes outstanding care of all of them – or does she? Something sinister bubbles under the surface – the happy animals are actually androids, and the real animals are held captive in a dungeon. They’re too messy and Zookeeper Frances can’t stand a mess! A rescue comes from a very unlikely source, and the final battle could go either way!

16983.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16983.description: Po and Tigress must track down and stop a messenger from delivering a scroll that could thrust China into all-out war!

16984.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16984.description: Po and the Furious Five meet their greatest challenge yet: a supernatural creature who is invincible to the powers of kung fu.

16985.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16985.description: Leo decides to sneak into Shredder's Lair alone only to face the biggest mutant threat yet.

16986.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16986.description: After an accident, Donnie finds himself slowly losing his intelligence.

16987.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16987.description: Pearl gets a job to be cool like her friends, but the only store that’s hiring is the lamest store at the mall! // SpongeBob loses the use of his thumbs, and must get them back in working order before his entire life falls apart.

16988.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16988.description: 'The Sharks' are the toughest guys in town, but their next confrontation might be too much for SpongeBob to handle. // Plankton clones SpongeBob in an effort to steal Krabs’ secret formula, but original Bob might ruin his plans.

16989.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16989.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick think their homes have been sold, they move away - much to Squidward’s delight. // When fortune cookies start predicting the future, Plankton realizes he can twist them to his own evil schemes.

16990.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16990.description: Thanks to Po, Hundun opens up his own noodle shop in the village, threatening to put Mr. Ping out of business.

16991.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16991.description: Over Po's objections, Shifu calls in a noble Samurai prawn to help take down a villain from Japan.

16992.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16992.description: A little girl loses her doll at the zoo, and Rico gives up his own doll to replace it. Private assures Rico that his good deed will come back to him. // When a raccoon shows up and starts stealing from the zoo animals, the penguins jump into action.

16993.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
16993.description: The penguins’ dolphin nemesis, Dr. Blowhole, is out for revenge. After Blowhole takes King Julien hostage, Skipper and gang must rush to rescue their annoying neighbor and stop evil Dr. Blowhole before he destroys the planet.

16994.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16994.description: When Raph makes a new friend in Zog, an alien Triceraton, he may have bitten off more than he can chew.

16995.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
16995.description: When the Turtles get word of the Kraang's return, they realize there is an even bigger threat coming to Earth!

16996.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16996.description: SpongeBob gets a pair of long pants, but they change his life in unexpected ways. // When Larry the Lobster opens a new gym in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob becomes his best customer.

16997.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16997.description: Sandy tries to study SpongeBob and Patrick’s behavior, but her science experiment goes horribly awry. // Mr. Krabs takes Plankton’s advice, and finally marries the only thing he ever loved…money!

16998.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
16998.description: Pearl gets a job to be cool like her friends, but the only store that’s hiring is the lamest store at the mall! // SpongeBob loses the use of his thumbs, and must get them back in working order before his entire life falls apart.

16999.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
16999.description: Shifu suggests Po takes a vow of silence to help him focus, but his plan goes awry when the panda starts an armed conflict by keeping his mouth shut.

17000.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17000.description: Once deemed a hero, cobra Fu-xi has turned renegade and is attacking the Valley of Peace. When the villagers adopt an anti-snake sentiment, will Viper help stop Fu-xi...or join him?

17001.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
17001.description: Julien is horrified when the baboons' dance routine gets more attention than his own. His attempts to sabotage the baboons blow up in his face. // There's a blackout and Julien convinces everyone they should revert to "jungle law" with him as king.

17002.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
17002.description: After an injury, Skipper goes to the vet for treatment. The rest of the team thinks he has turned into a zombie. // A hive of hornets has appeared at the entrance, and they refuse to leave. The penguins must find a way to dispose of the hornets.

17003.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
17003.description: In this special episode, we go back in time to the moment Appa was stolen, and find out exactly what happened to him, and where's he's been all this time - and where he is now!

17004.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
17004.description: While searching for Appa, the kids run into Jet, but are torn about whether to trust him or not. Meanwhile, Zuko also hunts for Appa.

17005.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17005.description: 'The Sharks' are the toughest guys in town, but their next confrontation might be too much for SpongeBob to handle. // Plankton clones SpongeBob in an effort to steal Krabs’ secret formula, but original Bob might ruin his plans.

17006.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17006.description: When SpongeBob and Patrick think their homes have been sold, they move away - much to Squidward’s delight. // When fortune cookies start predicting the future, Plankton realizes he can twist them to his own evil schemes.

17007.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17007.description: Sandy creates the latest acorn-based food sensation, but her tree pays the price for her greed. // SpongeBob erects a community bulletin board in the Krusty Krab, but anonymous reviews posted on it lead to trouble.

17008.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
17008.description: When the Turtles get word of the Kraang's return, they realize there is an even bigger threat coming to Earth!

17009.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
17009.description: When Shredder teams with the Kraang to receive a batch of mutagen, the Turtles' problems only get worse-even putting their friendship with April at stake.

17010.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17010.description: The local thugs love Mr. Ping's soup so much, the noodle shop becomes a villain hangout...with Mr. Ping as their unknowing crime boss!

17011.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
17011.description: Po befriends a group of young (and adorable) orphans-who also happen to be stealing money and goods from the villagers. Will Po be able to reform the kids or fall into the clutches of their evil leader?

17012.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
17012.description: When Skipper is knocked on the head, he's unable to lead the penguins on an important mission. The team scrambles to take his place, but they each have a hard time filling Skippers flippers./Private accidentally drinks Kowalski's truth serum and starts spilling the penguin's secrets to the rest of the zoo. Worst of all, he reveals they have been spying on their neighbors!

17013.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
17013.description: The lemurs argue, and Maurice and Mort move out of the habitat. Lonely Julien starts bugging the penguins, who decide they must get the lemurs back together. // A tiny frog with a nasty attitude moves to the zoo and starts terrorizing the animals.

17014.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
17014.description: When Burt the elephant asks the penguins to help him sneak out of the zoo, they take on the challenge and get the big guy out. // Marlene catches a glimpse of Fred the squirrel and falls in love at first sight.

17015.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17015.description: The gang heads to a food convention, but things go awry when they become stranded in the woods. // SpongeBob accidentally fibs to his pen pal, but when his friend comes to visit, he must keep the ruse going!

17016.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
17016.description: When SpongeBob hides the secret formula in his home, it’s up to Gary to protect it from Plankton. // When a freak accident causes everyone in town to become as stupid as Patrick, Sandy must save the day.
